.SH NAME
\f[CR]filessh\-config\f[R] \- configuration file for the
\f[CR]filessh\f[R] application.
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]filessh\f[R] configuration is managed through a TOML file.
The location of this file depends on the operating system.
For example, on Linux, it is typically located at
\f[CR]\(ti/.config/filessh/config.toml\f[R].
.SH DESCRIPTION
This man page documents the configuration system for the
\f[CR]filessh\f[R] crate.
The configuration is loaded from a \f[CR]config.toml\f[R] file and can
be overridden by environment variables.
The system allows for customization of application behavior, such as
logging levels and visual themes.
.PP
The configuration is parsed using the \f[CR]config\f[R] crate, which
allows for a hierarchical structure.
Settings can also be provided through environment variables prefixed
with \f[CR]FILESSH_\f[R].
For nested keys, use double underscores \f[CR]__\f[R] to separate them
(e.g., \f[CR]FILESSH_THEME__NAME=\(dqMyTheme\(dq\f[R]).
.SH CONFIGURATION FILES
\f[CR]filessh\f[R] attempts to load its configuration from a file named
\f[CR]config.toml\f[R] in the following locations, in order of
precedence:
.IP "1." 3
\f[B]Environment Variable\f[R]: The path specified by the
\f[CR]FILESSH_CONFIG\f[R] environment variable.
.IP "2." 3
\f[B]Platform\-Specific Directory\f[R]: The standard configuration
directory for the operating system:
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Linux\f[R]: \f[CR]$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/filessh/\f[R] or
\f[CR]$HOME/.config/filessh/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]macOS\f[R]: \f[CR]$HOME/Library/Application Support/filessh/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Windows\f[R]:
\f[CR]%LOCALAPPDATA%\(rsjayanaxhf\(rsfilessh\(rsconfig\(rs\f[R] (e.g.,
\f[CR]C:\(rsUsers\(rs<user>\(rsAppData\(rsLocal\(rsjayanaxhf\(rsfilessh\(rsconfig\(rs\f[R])
.RE
.IP "3." 3
\f[B]Fallback Directory\f[R]: A \f[CR].config\f[R] directory in the
current working directory.
.PP
If no configuration file is found, the application will proceed with the
default settings.
.SH CONFIGURATION OPTIONS
The following sections describe the available configuration options.
.SS Top\-Level Settings
These options are at the root of the configuration file.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]debug\f[R] (boolean): If \f[CR]true\f[R], sets the logging level
to \f[CR]DEBUG\f[R], providing verbose output for troubleshooting.
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]silent\f[R] (boolean): If \f[CR]true\f[R], suppresses all logging
output except for errors.
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.SS Theming (\f[CR][theme]\f[R])
The \f[CR]theme\f[R] section allows for customization of the
application\(cqs appearance.
You can either choose from a list of predefined default themes or define
your own custom theme.
.SS Using a Default Theme
To use a predefined theme, you can specify its name.
.PP
