.SS Defining a Custom Theme
To define a custom theme, you must provide a \f[CR][theme]\f[R] table
with the following keys:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]name\f[R] (string): The name of your custom theme.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]type_\f[R] (string): The type of theme.
Can be either \f[CR]\(dqDark\(dq\f[R] or \f[CR]\(dqShell\(dq\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]palette\f[R] (table): A table defining the colors used in the
theme.
.SS Palette (\f[CR][theme.palette]\f[R])
The \f[CR]palette\f[R] table requires a \f[CR]name\f[R] and a
comprehensive set of color definitions.
Colors should be specified as hex strings (e.g.,
\f[CR]\(dq#DEDFE3\(dq\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]name\f[R] (string): The name of the palette.
.PP
\f[B]Text Colors:\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
