.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Set a Default Theme
To set the theme to \f[CR]SolarizedDark\f[R], your
\f[CR]config.toml\f[R] would look like this:
.IP
.EX
theme = \(dqSolarizedDark\(dq
.EE
.SS Override Settings with Environment Variables
You can override any configuration setting using environment variables.
The variable name should be prefixed with \f[CR]FILESSH_\f[R], be in
uppercase, and use \f[CR]__\f[R] to separate keys.
.PP
To enable debug mode without modifying the configuration file:
.IP
.EX
export FILESSH_DEBUG=true
filessh
.EE
.PP
To change the theme name in a custom theme configuration:
.IP
.EX
export FILESSH_THEME__NAME=\(dqMy Special Theme\(dq
filessh
.EE
